## 5. Photos

### 5.1 Where photos are supported

| Level | Multiple photos | Required |
|-------|-----------------|----------|
| Rack | Yes | No |
| Row | Yes | No |
| Bin | Yes | No |
| Item | Yes | **Yes** |

### 5.2 Item photo rules

- **New items:** User must attach **at least one photo** before the item can be saved
- **Existing items:** UI warns and highlights items with zero photos; primary action becomes “Add photos”
- After creating an item with photos, user is taken to the item detail screen

### 5.3 How users add photos

Two explicit actions everywhere photos are supported:

| Button | Behaviour |
|--------|-----------|
| **Camera** | Opens device camera (rear camera preferred on phones) |
| **Gallery** | Opens photo library / file picker; **multiple selection** supported |

Additional on desktop:

- Drag and drop images onto the drop zone

### 5.4 Photo viewing & management

- Thumbnail grid for all photos at a level
- Tap zoom icon → full-screen lightbox
- Delete individual photos (with confirmation implied by action)
- Upload progress / loading state while images upload
- First photo at a level used as **card thumbnail** on parent grids/lists

### 5.5 Supported file types

Standard image formats: JPEG, PNG, GIF, WebP, HEIC/HEIF (where the device provides them).

